n especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":13,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":26,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":35,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes of Bownwys was born in 1302, in Bowness-on-Solway, Cumberland, England. She married Richard le Brun Lord of Drumburgh in 1324, in Bowness-on-Windermere, Westmorland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She lived in Cumberland, England, United Kingdom in 1337. She died in 1338, in Bowness-on-Solway, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1302–1338":"1302–1338","1305–1354":"1305–1354","1318–1396":"1318–1396","1396":"1396","Abt 1318":"umbes 1318","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1302":"1302","1324":"1324","about 1338":"umbes 1338","1453":"1453","1354":"1354","1318":"1318